        <h2 class="collectionAbout__subtitle subtitle"> Historical Landmarks</h2>
        <p class="collectionAbout__core core">The Belgian Ardennes have long stood as a place of mystery and beauty, their rolling hills and dense forests holding stories as old as time. Shrouded in mist and shaped by the passage of history, this region is more than just a landscape, it is a living testament to nature's quiet resilience. The rivers carve their way through valleys, their waters reflecting the ever-changing sky, while towering trees whisper with the wind, carrying secrets of centuries past.
        <br><br>
        Among the forests and winding waterways, deer move silently through the undergrowth, wild boars rustle through the leaves, and birds of prey soar overhead, watching from above. Ducks, a familiar sight in the region's many ponds and rivers, glide effortlessly across the water, their reflections rippling with each gentle movement.</p>

        <p class="collectionAbout__core core"> Whether wandering through its forests, sharing a meal by the fire, or simply watching the mist roll in over the hills, the feeling remains the same. No matter where you come from, the Ardennes have a way of making you feel at home.</p>
        <div class="collectionAbout__img"></div>
        <h2 class="collectionAbout__subtitle subtitle"> A Story Worth Telling</h2>
        <p class="collectionAbout__core core">While the Ardennes are known for the battles that once shook their soil, they are also a place of warmth, where traditions endure and hospitality runs deep. Small villages with stone houses and wooden beams invite visitors to slow down, to step inside and savor the simple pleasures of life. The region is rich in culinary delights—game meat, fresh trout, and the unmistakable scent of slow-cooked stews filling the air. Local cheeses, crafted with time-honored techniques, pair perfectly with a glass of Belgian beer, brewed in monasteries that have stood for generations.</p>
